<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-290-100  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 290 100.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacUser  May 1990 v6 n5 p43(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Letter Writer Plus. (Software Review) (PowerUp! Software Corp'sLetterWriter Plus desk accessory for creating quickcorrespondence)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wiggins, Robert R.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Power Up Software Corp. (products).andO;Product:   Letter Writer Plus (Utility program) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     Utility ProgramsEvaluation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Letter Writer PlusandM;Letter Writer Plus, formerly ExpressWrite (see Bobker's Dozen, April '90), isa handy DA for creating correspondence on the fly.andP;  To go along with its newname, it has been substantially revised and is a better program than itspredecessor.andP;  The interface has been improved.andP;  Its use of icons for mostcommon commands makes it unusually easy to learn.andP;  Basic forms such asletterheads can be saved as stationery, and regularly used text can be savedas &quot;paragraphs&quot; and inserted where needed with a click.andP;  The program's texthandling is good: Multiple styles and fonts are supported, but,unfortunately, tabs are not.andM;The program's packaging has also been improved.andP;  The manual is much betterthan the previous version, and to get you started, there's a selection of 50letters from the LetterWork collection (see Pinstripe Picks, March '90).andM;LetterWriter Plus now supports graphics for letterheads in a header area, butthat's the only area where graphics can be placed -- they're sorely missed inthe return addresses of envelopes.andP;  Still, Letter Writer Plus is an excellentenvelope printer.andP;  The mail-merge facility, which has always been excellentfor light- and medium-duty jobs, is enhanced by the ability to use AddressBook Plus files.andM;PowerUp!andP;  Software Corp., 2929 Campus Drive, San Mateo, CA 94403; (415)345-5900.andP;  Version 1.0.andP;  $89.95.andO;</TEXT></DOC>